y do people speak of horse sense\nwith such enthusiasm?\" \"Automobiles\nhaven't any of it\"\nDim STOPS\nSALE OFMLOMEL\n\u2022'Dodson's Liver Tone\" is Taking Place of Dangerous.\nSickening Chemical, Say Druggists\nEverv druggist in town has noticed\na great falling off in the salt of\ncalomel. They all give the siune rea\nson. Dodson's Liver Tone is taking\nIts place.\n\"Calomel is dangerous and people\nknow it.\" Dodson's Liver Tone is per\nsonally guaranteed by every druggist\n,vho sells it. A large bottle doesn't\ncost very much but if it fails to give\neasy relief in every case of liver slug\ngishness and constipation, just ask\nfor your money back.\nEvery Drop of Y our Blood\nShould Be Absolutely Pure\nAny slight disorder or impurities\nis a source of danger, as every vita]\norgan of the body depends upon the\nblood supply to properly perform\nits functions.\nMany painful and dangerous dis\neases are the direct result of a bad\ncondition of the blood. Among the\nmost serious are Rheumatism, with\nits torturing pain; Eczema. Tetter,\nErysipelas and other disfiguring\nskin diseases; general debility,\nwhich makes the strongest men\nhelpless, and many other diseases\nAnd many a girl's shirtwaist is rum\npled from too much pressing.\nKill That Cold With\nCASCARA QUININE\nFOR AND\nColds, Coughs La Grippo\nNeglected Colds are Dangerous\nTaka no chancas. Keep this standard remedy handy for the first sneeze.\nBreaks up a cold In 24 hours Relieves\nGrippe in 3 days\u2014Excellent for Headache\nQuinine In this form dee-j not effect the heed\u2014Cascara ia heat Tonic\nLaxative\u2014No Opiate in Hill's.\nALL DRUGGISTS SELL IT\nFOR THE BEST TABLES\nMAXWELL HOUSE\n'GOOD TO THE LAST DROP'\nSEALED TINS AT. GROCERS\nWhitman Sought by Collectors.\nWalt Whitman's manuscripts and\nfirst editions are now bringing high re\nturns to the rare book dealers. Ga\nbriel Wells, the dealer in fine books,\nhas sold the manuscript of the poem,\n\"After All Not to Create Only,\" for\n$1,500. The latter half of the poem Is\nwritten on the reverse side of the sta\ntionery of the United States treasury\ndepartment. In which Whitman was a\nclerk at the time. Commenting upon\nthe value of first editions of \"Leaves of\nGrass,\" Mr. Wells says that they have\ndoubled in value during the last five\nrears.\nIn Conclusion.\n\"Dot hoss was so slow,\" glowered\nIlastus over the remains of the unfor\ntunate equine that had just lost a\nrace over a railroad crossing, \"he was\nso slow dey ain't no boss in de world\ngo slower.\n\"Come de jedgment day and St. Pe\nter'll say, 'All yo' dead men come\nforth.' Den dey'll all come forth. Den\nhe'll say, 'All yo' dead ladies come\nforth.' Fin'ly he'll say, 'All yo' dead\nhorses come forth.'\n\"And jes' fo' spite dat hoss he'll\ncome fifth !\"\u2014American Legion Week\nly.\nIts Up toYbu as a Parent\nwhether you Peed your \"boy or\ngirt real building Food,or some\nthing that merely \"tastes good 1\nGrape=Nuts\nFurnishes exactly the food val\nues needed, to build young bod*\nies, and the taste is aeligHtFul\nGrocers everywhere sell this\nstaunch wheat and malted barley food\nHeady to eat'-Economical\nDodson's Liver Tone is a pieasanb\ntasting, purely vegetable remedy,\nharmless to both children and adults.\nTake a spoonful at night and wake up\nfeeling fine; no biliousness, sick head\nache, acid stomach or constipated\nbowels. It doesn't gripe or cause in\nconvenience all the next day like vio\nlent calomel. Take a dose of calomel\ntoday and tomorrow you will feel\nweak, sick and nauseated. Don't lose\na day.\u2014 Adv.\nare the direct result of impure\nblood.\nYou can in a large measure avoid\nliability to disease by the use of\nS. S. S., the wonderful blood rem\nedy that has been in constant use\nfor more than fifty years. S. S. S.\ncleanses the blood thoroughly. It\nis sold by druggists everywhere.\nFor valuable literature and med\nical advice absolutely free, write\ntoday to Chief Medical Adviser,\n159 Swift Laboratory, Atlanta, Ga.\nS. S. S. is not sold or recommended\nfor venereal diseases.\nFailure is pretty sure to find yet\nout if you think of it often enough.\nBelgian Fishing Industry.\nPlans are being drawn for the con\nstruction of a large fishing harbor In\nZeebrugge, which will not interfere\nwdth the w orking of the port as a com\nmercial center. This Is but a part of a\nproject for the establishment ofna\ntional fishing Industry. At present Bel\ngium is almost entirely dependent on\nforeign imports, especially of preserved\nfish. The building of the new harbor\nwill be undertaken by the government,\nwhich will also provide for the rapid\nhandling and transportation of goods;\nprivate enterprise will establish the\nnecessary cold storage and erect works\nfor making cases and barrels and fac\ntories for pickling, drying and pre\nserving fish.\nOne Would Be Happy.\nIt was the first night of the new\nplay\n\"I say,\" remarked the author to th*\nmanager, \"that scene-shifter over there\nIs a most peculiar looking fellow'.\"\n\"Yes; he's an Eskimo,\" said the\nmanager.\n\"An Eskimo! What on earth made\nyou take him on?\"\n\"Oh, I thought it would be a com\nfort to see one happy face if the plaj\nturns out to be a frost!\"","height":"23208","width":"15768"}}
